menu "PhoneBlock Dongle"

    config PHONEBLOCK_BASE_URL
        string "PhoneBlock API base URL"
        default "https://phoneblock.net/phoneblock/api"
        help
            Base URL for the PhoneBlock REST API. Endpoints are appended
            as /num/{phone}, /rate, etc.

            Two endpoints exist:
              * https://phoneblock.net/phoneblock/api  — production
              * https://phoneblock.net/pb-test/api     — test instance

            A token is bound to exactly one instance. Tokens generated on
            the test instance only work there, and vice versa. The token
            prefix (pbt_) is the same in both cases.

    config SIP_REGISTRAR_PORT
        int "SIP registrar port"
        default 5060
        range 1 65535
        help
            Default port written into NVS when the user does not
            override it through the web UI. Registrar host, username
            and password are not configurable via Kconfig — they go
            through the setup wizard.

    config SIP_EXPIRES
        int "Registration expiry (seconds)"
        default 600
        range 60 86400
        help
            Requested lifetime of the REGISTER binding. The dongle
            refreshes halfway through this interval.

    config SIP_CONTACT_HOST_OVERRIDE
        string "Override local host in Via/Contact (for NAT debugging)"
        default ""
        help
            When running inside QEMU user-mode networking, the ESP32's
            local IP (e.g. 10.0.2.15) is only reachable from within the
            emulator. The Fritz!Box cannot deliver an INVITE to that
            address. Set this to the host-visible address (typically the
            workstation's LAN IP, e.g. 192.168.178.22) and combine with
            `-nic user,model=open_eth,hostfwd=udp::5061-:5061` in QEMU.
            Leave empty to advertise the actual local interface IP,
            which is the correct behavior on real hardware.

    config SIP_CONTACT_PORT_OVERRIDE
        int "Override local SIP port in Via/Contact (0 = no override)"
        default 0
        range 0 65535
        help
            If the hostfwd maps a different host port to the guest, set
            it here. 0 means "advertise the bound UDP port".

    config SIP_TEST_FORCE_SPAM_STAR_NUMBERS
        bool "Test hook: treat *-prefix callers as SPAM"
        default n
        help
            For development only: when enabled, calls from numbers
            starting with '*' (Fritz!Box internal dial codes like
            **622 or *21#) are treated as SPAM and answered with
            200 OK + tone + BYE, bypassing both the display-name
            phone-book skip and the PhoneBlock API.

            Lets you exercise the full answer + audio + hangup path
            by calling your IP-phone extension from another internal
            Fritz!Box phone, without blacklisting a real number.
            Leave disabled in production.

    config RTP_PLAY_ANNOUNCEMENT
        bool "Play embedded voice announcement to spam callers"
        default y
        help
            When enabled, answered spam calls stream the audio file
            embedded from main/audio/announcement.alaw to the caller
            (G.711 A-law, 8 kHz, 20 ms frames) before BYE. Disable to
            send BYE immediately after ACK (silent pickup, old behavior).

endmenu
